data.name: Paras
data.flavorText: The mushrooms, known as tochukaso, are controlling the bug. Even if the bug bugs the mushrooms, they tell it to bug off.

attacks.name: Absorb
attacks.text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokémon.

data.name: Beautifly
data.flavorText: It has an aggressive nature. It stabs prey with its long, narrow mouth to drain the prey's fluids.

abilities.name: Stoked Straw
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand.

attacks.name: Mega Drain
attacks.text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

data.name: Trevenant
data.flavorText: People fear it due to a belief that it devours any who try to cut down trees in its forest, but to the Pokémon it shares its woods with, it's kind.

abilities.name: Elder Tree Barrier
abilities.text: If this Pokémon is Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent's Pokémon V, your opponent can't take any Prize cards for it.

attacks.name: Giga Impact
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

data.name: Slugma
data.flavorText: Its body is made of magma. If it doesn't keep moving, its body will cool and harden.

attacks.name: Draw In
attacks.text: Attach a Fire Energy card from your discard pile to this Pokémon.

data.name: Oddish
data.flavorText: If exposed to moonlight, it starts to move. It roams far and wide at night to scatter its seeds.

data.name: Magcargo
data.flavorText: Its body is as hot as lava and is always billowing. Flames will occasionally burst from its shell.

attacks.name: Lost Volcano
attacks.text: Put all Energy attached to this Pokémon in the Lost Zone.

data.name: Vileplume
data.flavorText: It has the world's largest petals. With every step, the petals shake out heavy clouds of toxic pollen.

attacks.name: Mega Drain
attacks.text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Allergy Storm
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, they can't play any Supporter cards from their hand. If tails, during your opponent's next turn, they can't play any Item cards from their hand.

data.name: Delphox V
rules: V rule: When your Pokémon V is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Eerie Glow
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned and Confused.

attacks.name: Magical Fire
attacks.text: Put 2 Energy attached to this Pokémon in the Lost Zone. This attack also does 120 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

data.name: Wurmple
data.flavorText: It lives among the tall grass and in forests. It repels attacks by raising up the spikes on its rear.

attacks.name: Creepy-Crawly Congregation
attacks.text: Search your deck for any number of Wurmple, Silcoon, Beautifly, Cascoon, and Dustox, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

data.name: Politoed
data.flavorText: At nightfall, these Pokémon appear on the shores of lakes. They announce their territorial claims by letting out cries that sound like shouting.

attacks.name: Lordly Songleader
attacks.text: If Poliwag is on your Bench, this attack does 60 more damage. If Poliwhirl is on your Bench, this attack does 90 more damage. If Poliwrath is on your Bench, this attack does 120 more damage.

data.name: Silcoon
data.flavorText: It drinks dew that collects on its silk and waits for evolution. Its hard cocoon repels attacks.

attacks.name: Entangling String
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't attack.

data.name: Seel
data.flavorText: Thanks to its thick fat, cold seas don't bother it at all, but it gets tired pretty easily in warm waters.

data.name: Nuzleaf
data.flavorText: It lives deep in forests. With the leaf on its head, it makes a flute whose song makes listeners uneasy.

attacks.name: Push Down
attacks.text: You may have your opponent switch their Active Pokémon with 1 of their Benched Pokémon.

data.name: Horsea
data.flavorText: Horsea makes its home in oceans with gentle currents. If this Pokémon is under attack, it spits out pitch-black ink and escapes.

attacks.name: Reverse Thrust
attacks.text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

data.name: Roserade
data.flavorText: After captivating opponents with its sweet scent, it lashes them with its thorny whips.

attacks.name: Poisonous Whip
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

attacks.name: Assassin's Rose
attacks.text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is affected by a Special Condition, this attack also does 60 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

data.name: Finneon
data.flavorText: It lures in prey with its shining tail fins. It stays near the surface during the day and moves to the depths when night falls.

abilities.name: Oceanic Accompaniment
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn, you may attach a Water Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Pokémon that has the Swim Freely attack.

data.name: Dottler
data.flavorText: It barely moves, but it's still alive. Hiding in its shell without food or water seems to have awakened its psychic powers.

attacks.name: Barrier Attack
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

data.name: Hisuian Basculin
data.flavorText: Though it differs from other Basculin in several respects, including demeanor—this one is gentle—I have categorized it as a regional form given the vast array of shared qualities.

attacks.name: Surprise Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

data.name: Litwick
data.flavorText: The flame on its head keeps its body slightly warm. This Pokémon takes lost children by the hand to guide them to the spirit world.

attacks.name: Kindling Panic
attacks.text: Discard the top card of your opponent's deck.

data.name: Lampent
data.flavorText: This Pokémon appears just before someone passes away, so it's feared as an emissary of death.

attacks.name: Flickering Glow
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

data.name: Chandelure
data.flavorText: This Pokémon haunts dilapidated mansions. It sways its arms to hypnotize opponents with the ominous dancing of its flames.

abilities.name: Mountain Roasting
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may discard the top 3 cards of your opponent's deck.

data.name: Pyroar
data.flavorText: The temperature of its breath is over 10,000 degrees Fahrenheit, but Pyroar doesn't use it on its prey. This Pokémon prefers to eat raw meat.

abilities.name: Scorching Aura
abilities.text: During Pokémon Checkup, put 4 damage counters on your opponent's Burned Pokémon instead of 2.

attacks.name: Fire Fang
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.

data.name: Poliwag
data.flavorText: For Poliwag, swimming is easier than walking. The swirl pattern on its belly is actually part of the Pokémon's innards showing through the skin.

attacks.name: Splashing Dodge
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokémon.

data.name: Lumineon
data.flavorText: They traverse the deep waters as if crawling over the seafloor. The fantastic lights of its fins shine like stars in the night sky.

attacks.name: Swim Freely
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokémon.

data.name: Snover
data.flavorText: One is likely to encounter this Pokémon while out in the snow. There are stories of Snover appearing in human settlements but doing no harm—rather, they bond with the children.

data.name: Gloom
data.flavorText: Its pistils exude an incredibly foul odor. The horrid stench can cause fainting at a distance of 1.25 miles.

attacks.name: Absorb
attacks.text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

data.name: Parasect
data.flavorText: The bug is mostly dead, with the mushroom on its back having become the main body. If the mushroom comes off, the bug stops moving.

abilities.name: Lethargy Spores
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may make both Active Pokémon Asleep and Poisoned.

attacks.name: X-Scissor
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 50 more damage.

data.name: Cascoon
data.flavorText: It never forgets any attack it endured while in the cocoon. After evolution, it seeks payback.

attacks.name: Harden
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks if that damage is 60 or less.

data.name: Dustox
data.flavorText: Tends to be drawn to bonfires on dark nights. Difficult to chase away from settlements because of the way it scatters highly toxic scales.

attacks.name: Nadir Powder
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused and Poisoned. During Pokémon Checkup, put 8 damage counters on that Pokémon instead of 1.

data.name: Roselia
data.flavorText: Its flowers give off a relaxing fragrance. The stronger its aroma, the healthier the Roselia is.

attacks.name: Soothing Scent
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

data.name: Torkoal
data.flavorText: It burns coal inside its shell for energy. It blows out black soot if it is endangered.

attacks.name: Flamethrower
attacks.text: Discard an Energy from this Pokémon.

data.name: Litleo
data.flavorText: This hot-blooded Pokémon is filled with curiosity. When it gets angry or starts fighting, its short mane gets hot.

attacks.name: Singe
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.

data.name: Dewgong
data.flavorText: It sunbathes on the beach after meals. The rise in its body temperature helps its digestion.

attacks.name: Swim Freely
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Floe Return
attacks.text: Shuffle any amount of Water Energy from your Pokémon into your deck. This attack does 40 damage for each card you shuffled into your deck in this way.

data.name: Luvdisc
data.flavorText: Luvdisc makes its home in coral reefs in warm seas. It especially likes sleeping in the space between Corsola's branches.

attacks.name: Matching Look
attacks.text: Each player reveals the top 2 cards of their deck, then draws those cards.

data.name: Abomasnow
data.flavorText: If it sees any packs of Darumaka going after Snover, it chases them off, swinging its sizable arms like hammers.

attacks.name: Double-Edge
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

data.name: Seedot
data.flavorText: If it remains still, it looks just like a real nut. It delights in surprising foraging Pokémon.

attacks.name: Absorb
attacks.text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokémon.

data.name: Shiftry
data.flavorText: A Pokémon that was feared as a forest guardian. It can read the foe's mind and take preemptive action.

attacks.name: Fan Tornado
attacks.text: You may have your opponent switch their Active Pokémon with 1 of their Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Tearing Gust
attacks.text: Put this Pokémon and all attached cards in the Lost Zone.

data.name: Phantump
data.flavorText: After a lost child perished in the forest, their spirit possessed a tree stump, causing the spirit's rebirth as this Pokémon.

data.name: Blipbug
data.flavorText: A constant collector of information, this Pokémon is very smart. Very strong is what it isn't.

data.name: Orbeetle
data.flavorText: It's famous for its high level of intelligence, and the large size of its brain is proof that it also possesses immense psychic power.

abilities.name: Jamming Attachment
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may attach up to 3 Energy cards from your opponent's discard pile to your opponent's Pokémon in any way you like.

attacks.name: Mysterious Wave
attacks.text: This attack does 50 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

data.name: Poliwhirl
data.flavorText: Staring at the swirl on its belly causes drowsiness. This trait of Poliwhirl's has been used in place of lullabies to get children to go to sleep.

attacks.name: Double Smash
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 50 damage for each heads.

data.name: Seadra
data.flavorText: It's the males that raise the offspring. While Seadra are raising young, the spines on their backs secrete thicker and stronger poison.

attacks.name: Swim Freely
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Hydro Jet
attacks.text: This attack does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon for each Water Energy attached to this Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

data.name: Kingdra
data.flavorText: With the arrival of a storm at sea, this Pokémon will show itself on the surface. When a Kingdra and a Dragonite meet, a fierce battle ensues.

abilities.name: Seething Currents
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may have either player shuffle their hand and put it on the bottom of their deck. If that player put any cards on the bottom of their deck in this way, they draw 4 cards.

data.name: Shellos
data.flavorText: There's speculation that its appearance is determined by what it eats, but the truth remains elusive.

data.name: Hisuian Basculegion
data.flavorText: Clads itself in the souls of comrades that perished before fulfilling their goals of journeying upstream. No other species throughout all Hisui's rivers is Basculegion's equal.

attacks.name: Upstream Spirits
attacks.text: This attack does 20 damage for each basic Energy card in your discard pile. Then, shuffle those cards into your deck.

attacks.name: Water Shot
attacks.text: Discard an Energy from this Pokémon.

data.name: Cramorant
data.flavorText: It's so strong that it can knock out some opponents in a single hit, but it also may forget what it's battling midfight.

abilities.name: Lost Provisions
abilities.text: If you have 4 or more cards in the Lost Zone, ignore all Energy in this Pokémon's attack costs.

attacks.name: Spit Innocently
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness.

data.name: Raichu
data.flavorText: Its long tail serves as a ground to protect itself from its own high-voltage power.

attacks.name: Thunder Shock
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Ace Spark
attacks.text: If you have used your VSTAR Power, this attack does 120 more damage.

data.name: Gastly
data.flavorText: Born from gases, anyone would faint if engulfed by its gaseous body, which contains poison.

attacks.name: Furtive Drop
attacks.text: Put 1 damage counter on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

data.name: Radiant Gardevoir
data.flavorText: It has the power to predict the future. Its power peaks when it is protecting its Trainer.
rules: Radiant Pokémon Rule: You can't have more than 1 Radiant Pokémon in your deck.

abilities.name: Loving Veil
abilities.text: All of your Pokémon take 20 less damage from attacks from your opponent's Pokémon V (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Psychic
attacks.text: This attack does 20 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

data.name: Hisuian Zoroark
data.flavorText: With its disheveled white fur, it looks like an embodiment of death. Heedless of its own safety, Zoroark attacks its nemeses with a bitter energy so intense, it lacerates Zoroark's own body.

attacks.name: Doom Curse
attacks.text: At the end of your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon will be Knocked Out.

attacks.name: Call Back
attacks.text: Put a card from your discard pile into your hand.

data.name: Inkay
data.flavorText: It spins while making its luminescent spots flash. These spots allow it to communicate with others by using different patterns of light.

attacks.name: Fickle Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

data.name: Hisuian Growlithe
data.flavorText: They patrol their territory in pairs. I believe the igneous rock components in the fur of this species are the result of volcanic activity in its habitat.

attacks.name: Singe
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.

data.name: Ducklett
data.flavorText: They are better at swimming than flying, and they happily eat their favorite food, peat moss, as they dive underwater.

data.name: Hisuian Arcanine
data.flavorText: Snaps at its foes with fangs cloaked in blazing flame. Despite its bulk, it deftly feints every which way, leading opponents on a deceptively merry chase as it all but dances around them.

attacks.name: Very Vulnerable
attacks.text: If you have no cards in your hand, this attack does 150 more damage.

data.name: Machop
data.flavorText: Its whole body is composed of muscles. Even though it's the size of a human child, it can hurl 100 grown-ups.

data.name: Kyurem VMAX
rules: VMAX rule: When your Pokémon VMAX is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 3 Prize cards.

abilities.name: Glaciated World
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may discard the top card of your deck. If that card is a Water Energy card, attach it to 1 of your Pokémon.

attacks.name: Max Frost
attacks.text: You may discard any amount of Water Energy from this Pokémon. This attack does 50 more damage for each card you discarded in this way.

data.name: Machamp
data.flavorText: It quickly swings its four arms to rock its opponents with ceaseless punches and chops from all angles.

abilities.name: Crisis Muscles
abilities.text: If your opponent has 3 or fewer Prize cards remaining, this Pokémon gets +150 HP.

attacks.name: Strong-Arm Lariat
attacks.text: You may do 100 more damage. If you do, during your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

data.name: Glastrier
data.flavorText: Glastrier emits intense cold from its hooves. It's also a belligerent Pokémon—anything it wants, it takes by force.

attacks.name: Freeze Down
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon is a Basic Pokémon, it can't attack during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Wild Tackle
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

data.name: Gliscor
data.flavorText: Its flight is soundless. It uses its lengthy tail to carry off its prey... Then its elongated fangs do the rest.

attacks.name: Hurricane Shock
attacks.text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 50 damage for each heads. If at least 2 of them are heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

data.name: Pikachu
data.flavorText: Pikachu that can generate powerful electricity have cheek sacs that are extra soft and super stretchy.

abilities.name: Pika Dash
abilities.text: If this Pokémon has any Energy attached, it has no Retreat Cost.

attacks.name: Whimsy Tackle
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

data.name: Makuhita
data.flavorText: There's a rumor of a traditional recipe for stew that Trainers can use to raise strong Makuhita.

attacks.name: Fake Out
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

data.name: Electrike
data.flavorText: It stores static electricity in its fur for discharging. It gives off sparks if a storm approaches.

attacks.name: Thunder Fang
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

data.name: Mienfoo
data.flavorText: In one minute, a well-trained Mienfoo can chop with its arms more than 100 times.

data.name: Rotom V
rules: V rule: When your Pokémon V is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

abilities.name: Instant Charge
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may draw 3 cards. If you use this Ability, your turn ends.

attacks.name: Scrap Short
attacks.text: Put any number of Pokémon Tool cards from your discard pile in the Lost Zone. This attack does 40 more damage for each card you put in the Lost Zone in this way.

data.name: Ariados
data.flavorText: It spews threads from its mouth to catch its prey. When night falls, it leaves its web to go hunt aggressively.

attacks.name: String Bind
attacks.text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Colorless in your opponent's Active Pokémon's Retreat Cost.

attacks.name: Venomous Fang
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

data.name: Eelektrik
data.flavorText: These Pokémon have a big appetite. When they spot their prey, they attack it and paralyze it with electricity.

abilities.name: Ad Hoc Shock
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

data.name: Spiritomb
data.flavorText: Exactly 108 spirits gathered to become this Pokémon. Apparently there are some ill-natured spirits in the mix.

abilities.name: Cursed Message
abilities.text: If this Pokémon is Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent's Pokémon, search your deck for a card and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Chain of Spirits
attacks.text: This attack does 60 more damage for each Spiritomb in your discard pile.

data.name: Clefable
data.flavorText: A timid fairy Pokémon that is rarely seen, it will run and hide the moment it senses people.

abilities.name: Spirit Charm
abilities.text: All of your Pokémon take 30 less damage from attacks from your opponent's Dragon Pokémon (after applying Weakness and Resistance). You can't apply more than 1 Spirit Charm Ability at a time.

data.name: Drapion V
rules: V rule: When your Pokémon V is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

abilities.name: Wild Style
abilities.text: This Pokémon's attacks cost Colorless less for each of your opponent's Single Strike, Rapid Strike, and Fusion Strike Pokémon in play.

attacks.name: Dynamic Tail
attacks.text: This attack also does 60 damage to 1 of your Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

data.name: Haunter
data.flavorText: This frightful, malevolent spirit can glide through walls, appearing wherever it likes. According to rumor, victims of a Haunter's lick will wither to death day by day.

attacks.name: Cursed Drop
attacks.text: Put 3 damage counters on your opponent's Pokémon in any way you like.

data.name: Darkrai
data.flavorText: On a moonless night, a strange incident occurred in which every one of a village's inhabitants suffered nightmares. The villagers attested that Darkrai appeared before them in these nightmares.

attacks.name: Nightmare
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Pitch-Black Blade
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

data.name: Jynx
data.flavorText: Its strange cries sound like human language. There are some musicians who compose songs for Jynx to sing.

attacks.name: Alluring Dance
attacks.text: Switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon with their Active Pokémon. The new Active Pokémon is now Confused.

data.name: Hoopa
data.flavorText: It gathers things it likes and passes them through its loop to teleport them to a secret place.

attacks.name: Hand of Djinn
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Darkness Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.

data.name: Sableye
data.flavorText: This Pokémon is feared. When its gemstone eyes begin to glow with a sinister shine, it's believed that Sableye will steal people's spirits away.

attacks.name: Lost Mine
attacks.text: You can use this attack only if you have 10 or more cards in the Lost Zone. Put 12 damage counters on your opponent's Pokémon in any way you like.

data.name: Radiant Hisuian Sneasler
data.flavorText: Because of Sneasler's virulent poison and daunting physical prowess, no other species could hope to best it on the frozen highlands. Preferring solitude, this species does not form packs.
rules: Radiant Pokémon Rule: You can't have more than 1 Radiant Pokémon in your deck.

abilities.name: Poison Peak
abilities.text: During Pokémon Checkup, put 2 more damage counters on your opponent's Poisoned Pokémon.

attacks.name: Poison Jab
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

data.name: Hisuian Zorua
data.flavorText: A once-departed soul, returned to life in Hisui. Derives power from resentment, which rises as energy atop its head and takes on the forms of foes. In this way, Zorua vents lingering malice.

attacks.name: Collect
attacks.text: Draw a card.

data.name: Bronzor
data.flavorText: It appears in ancient ruins. The pattern on its body doesn't come from any culture in the Galar region, so it remains shrouded in mystery.

data.name: Malamar
data.flavorText: Gazing at its luminescent spots will quickly induce a hypnotic state, putting the observer under Malamar's control.

attacks.name: Synchro Kinesis
attacks.text: Each player reveals their hand. If a card in your opponent's hand has the same name as a card in your hand, this attack does 90 more damage.

data.name: Lickitung
data.flavorText: If this Pokémon's sticky saliva gets on you and you don't clean it off, an intense itch will set in. The itch won't go away, either.

data.name: Spectrier
data.flavorText: It probes its surroundings with all its senses save one—it doesn't use its sense of sight. Spectrier's kicks are said to separate soul from body.

attacks.name: Night Footsteps
attacks.text: Choose 2 of your opponent's Pokémon and put 2 damage counters on each of them.

attacks.name: Phantom Strike
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't use Phantom Strike.

data.name: Porygon
data.flavorText: State-of-the-art technology was used to create Porygon. It was the first artificial Pokémon to be created via computer programming.

attacks.name: Branch Calculation
attacks.text: Look at the top 4 cards of either player's deck and put them back in any order.

data.name: Poliwrath
data.flavorText: Its body is solid muscle. When swimming through cold seas, Poliwrath uses its impressive arms to smash through drift ice and plow forward.

attacks.name: Split Spiral Punch
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

attacks.name: Splash Loop
attacks.text: Put 2 Energy attached to this Pokémon into your hand.

data.name: Porygon-Z
data.flavorText: Porygon-Z had a program installed to allow it to move between dimensions, but the program also caused instability in Porygon-Z's behavior.

attacks.name: Downgrading Beam
attacks.text: Devolve 1 of your opponent's evolved Pokémon by removing any number of Evolution cards from it. Your opponent shuffles those cards into their deck.

data.name: Aerodactyl V
rules: V rule: When your Pokémon V is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Rock Crush
attacks.text: Discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

data.name: Ambipom
data.flavorText: It uses its tails for everything. If it wraps both of its tails around you and gives you a squeeze, that's proof it really likes you.

attacks.name: All-You-Can-Grab
attacks.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. Search your deck for a number of cards up to the number of heads and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Knock Off
attacks.text: Discard a random card from your opponent's hand.

data.name: Aerodactyl VSTAR
rules: VSTAR rule: When your Pokémon VSTAR is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Lost Dive
attacks.text: Put the top 3 cards of your deck in the Lost Zone.

attacks.name: Ancient Star
attacks.text: Until this Pokémon leaves play, it gains an Ability that has the effect "Your opponent's Pokémon V in play, except any Aerodactyl VSTAR, have no Abilities." (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)

data.name: Bouffalant
data.flavorText: These Pokémon can crush a car with no more than a headbutt. Bouffalant with more hair on their heads hold higher positions within the herd.

attacks.name: Lost Headbutt
attacks.text: Put an Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon in the Lost Zone.

data.name: Relicanth
data.flavorText: Rock-hard scales and oil-filled swim bladders allow this Pokémon to survive the intense water pressure of the deep sea.

attacks.name: Into the Deep
attacks.text: Put up to 2 basic Energy cards from your discard pile into your hand.

data.name: Komala
data.flavorText: It remains asleep from birth to death as a result of the sedative properties of the leaves that form its diet.

abilities.name: All Just a Dream
abilities.text: If this Pokémon is Asleep and is Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent's Pokémon, your opponent can't take any Prize cards for it.

attacks.name: Collapse
attacks.text: This Pokémon is now Asleep.

data.name: Carbink
data.flavorText: When beset by attackers, Carbink wipes them all out by firing high-energy beams from the gems embedded in its body.

data.name: Tynamo
data.flavorText: One alone can emit only a trickle of electricity, so a group of them gathers to unleash a powerful electric shock.

attacks.name: Call Sign
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Lightning Pokémon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

data.name: Gengar
data.flavorText: On the night of a full moon, if shadows move on their own and laugh, it must be Gengar's doing.

abilities.name: Netherworld Gate
abilities.text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is in your discard pile, you may put it onto your Bench. If you do, put 3 damage counters on this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Screaming Circle
attacks.text: Put 2 damage counters on your opponent's Active Pokémon for each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

data.name: Mr. Mime
data.flavorText: The behavior of this clown-like Pokémon reminds one of pantomime. It creates invisible walls using a force emitted from its fingertips.

attacks.name: Tricky Slap
attacks.text: You and your opponent play Rock-Paper-Scissors until someone wins. If you win, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokémon.

data.name: Banette
data.flavorText: Resentment at being cast off made it spring into being. Some say that treating it well will satisfy it, and it will once more become a stuffed toy.

abilities.name: Puppet Offering
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may put a Supporter card from your discard pile into your hand. If you do, put this Pokémon in the Lost Zone. (Discard all attached cards.)

data.name: Cresselia
data.flavorText: Those who sleep holding Cresselia's feather are assured of joyful dreams. It is said to represent the crescent moon.

attacks.name: Moonglow Reverse
attacks.text: Move 2 damage counters from each of your Pokémon to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.

data.name: Comfey
data.flavorText: Comfey picks flowers with its vine and decorates itself with them. For some reason, flowers won't wither once they're attached to a Comfey.

abilities.name: Flower Selecting
abilities.text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, you may look at the top 2 cards of your deck and put 1 of them into your hand. Put the other card in the Lost Zone.

data.name: Machoke
data.flavorText: A sturdy creature boasting a robust physique and boundless stamina. Loves training above all else and voluntarily assists with tasks such as construction and clearing land.

data.name: Rhyhorn
data.flavorText: Strong, but not too bright, this Pokémon can shatter even a skyscraper with its charging tackles.

attacks.name: Take Down
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 20 damage to itself.

data.name: Rhydon
data.flavorText: It begins walking on its hind legs after evolution. It can punch holes through boulders with its horn.

attacks.name: Take Down
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

data.name: Sudowoodo
data.flavorText: Though it pretends to be a tree, it fails to fool even children. To the touch, its body feels more like rock than tree bark. Sudowoodo's extreme aversion to water merits special note.

attacks.name: Joust
attacks.text: Before doing damage, discard all Pokémon Tools from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Impound
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't retreat.

data.name: Gligar
data.flavorText: It flies straight at its target's face, then clamps down on the startled victim to inject poison.

attacks.name: Cyclone Pincers
attacks.text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

data.name: Hariyama
data.flavorText: Hariyama that are big and fat aren't necessarily strong. There are some small ones that move nimbly and use moves skillfully.

attacks.name: Shove
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Muscular Slap
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.

data.name: Meditite
data.flavorText: It eats just one berry a day. By enduring hunger, its spirit is tempered and made sharper.

attacks.name: Focus Fist
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

data.name: Gastrodon
data.flavorText: Its search for food sometimes leads it onto land, where it leaves behind a sticky trail of slime as it passes through.

attacks.name: Recover
attacks.text: Discard an Energy from this Pokémon and heal all damage from it.

attacks.name: Earthquake
attacks.text: This attack also does 20 damage to each of your Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

data.name: Mienshao
data.flavorText: When Mienshao comes across a truly challenging opponent, it will lighten itself by biting off the fur on its arms.

attacks.name: Double Smash
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 70 damage for each heads.

data.name: Landorus
data.flavorText: From the forces of lightning and wind, it creates energy to give nutrients to the soil and make the land abundant.

attacks.name: Smashing Edge
attacks.text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokémon.

data.name: Binacle
data.flavorText: After two Binacle find a suitably sized rock, they adhere themselves to it and live together. They cooperate to gather food during high tide.

data.name: Barbaracle
data.flavorText: Seven Binacle come together to form one Barbaracle. The Binacle that serves as the head gives orders to those serving as the limbs.

abilities.name: Lost Block
abilities.text: Your opponent puts any Prize cards they would take in the Lost Zone instead of into their hand.

data.name: Falinks
data.flavorText: Five of them are troopers, and one is the brass. The brass's orders are absolute.

attacks.name: Fighting Headbutt
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness. If your opponent's Active Pokémon is a Pokémon V, this attack does 50 more damage.

data.name: Honchkrow
data.flavorText: Its goons take care of most of the fighting for it. The only time it dirties its own hands is in delivering a final blow to finish off an opponent.

attacks.name: Night Cyclone
attacks.text: Move all Energy from this Pokémon to your Benched Pokémon in any way you like.

data.name: Radiant Steelix
data.flavorText: It is said that if an Onix lives for over 100 years, its composition changes to become diamond-like.
rules: Radiant Pokémon Rule: You can't have more than 1 Radiant Pokémon in your deck.

attacks.name: Energy Stream
attacks.text: Attach up to 2 Metal Energy cards from your discard pile to this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Destructive Finish
attacks.text: Discard cards from the top of your deck until only 1 card remains. This attack does 30 more damage for each Energy card you discarded in this way.

data.name: Galarian Stunfisk
data.flavorText: Living in mud with a high iron content has given it a strong steel body.

attacks.name: Field Trap
attacks.text: If your opponent has a Stadium in play, discard it. If you discarded a Stadium in this way, discard 2 Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

data.name: Lickilicky
data.flavorText: Lickilicky's strange tongue can stretch to many times the length of its body. No one has figured out how Lickilicky's tongue can stretch so far.

data.name: Snorlax
data.flavorText: It is not satisfied unless it eats over 880 pounds of food every day. When it is done eating, it goes promptly to sleep.

abilities.name: Unfazed Fat
abilities.text: Prevent all effects of attacks from your opponent's Pokémon done to this Pokémon. (Damage is not an effect.)

attacks.name: Thumping Snore
attacks.text: This Pokémon is now Asleep. During Pokémon Checkup, flip 2 coins instead of 1. If either of them is tails, this Pokémon is still Asleep.

data.name: Hisuian Zoroark V
rules: V rule: When your Pokémon V is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Void Return
attacks.text: You may switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Shadow Cyclone
attacks.text: Move an Energy from this Pokémon to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

data.name: Skwovet
data.flavorText: Found throughout the Galar region, this Pokémon becomes uneasy if its cheeks are ever completely empty of berries.

data.name: Damage Pump
rules: Move up to 2 damage counters from 1 of your Pokémon to your other Pokémon in any way you like.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

data.name: Gift Energy
rules: As long as this card is attached to a Pokémon, it provides Colorless Energy. If the Pokémon this card is attached to is Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent's Pokémon, draw cards until you have 7 cards in your hand.

data.name: Giratina V
rules: V rule: When your Pokémon V is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Abyss Seeking
attacks.text: Look at the top 4 cards of your deck and put 2 of them into your hand. Put the other cards in the Lost Zone.

attacks.name: Shred
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

data.name: Miss Fortune Sisters
rules: Look at the top 5 cards of your opponent's deck and discard any number of Item cards you find there. Your opponent shuffles the other cards back into their deck.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

data.name: Thorton
rules: Choose a Basic Pokémon in your discard pile and switch it with 1 of your Basic Pokémon in play. Any attached cards, damage counters, Special Conditions, turns in play, and any other effects remain on the new Pokémon.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

data.name: Hisuian Zoroark VSTAR
rules: VSTAR rule: When your Pokémon VSTAR is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

abilities.name: Phantom Star
abilities.text: During your turn, you may discard your hand and draw 7 cards. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)

attacks.name: Ticking Curse
attacks.text: This attack does 50 damage for each of your Pokémon that has any damage counters on it.

data.name: Box of Disaster
rules: If the Pokémon V this card is attached to has full HP and is Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent's Pokémon, put 8 damage counters on the Attacking Pokémon.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.
Attach a Pokémon Tool to 1 of your Pokémon that doesn't already have a Pokémon Tool attached.

data.name: Collapsed Stadium
rules: Each player can't have more than 4 Benched Pokémon. If a player has 5 or more Benched Pokémon, they discard Benched Pokémon until they have 4 Pokémon on the Bench. The player who played this card discards first. If more than one effect changes the number of Benched Pokémon allowed, use the smaller number.
